Description:
The DiagnosticReport FHIR resource represents resulted diagnostic orders and relevant data associated with the order and the patient. Supported diagnostic services include laboratory, radiology, and cardiology. Within DiagnosticReport, the Observation FHIR resource returns individual components from laboratory tests and text-based content, such as narratives or impressions, from radiology and cardiology results. This resource returns textual results and discrete result components. It can return lab, imaging, and cardiology results. It can also return micro and EKG and pathology results that are not a scan. Scans filed into Epic are not returned by this resource.

The DiagnosticReport resource corresponds to the following Common Clinical Data Set (CCDS) Elements: Laboratory Tests.

The search interaction for DiagnosticReport enables the client to query for diagnostic reports based on a patient and additional optional parameters, such as date, LOINC code/Identity ID, or order ID/accession number. Client may use the Patient Identifier Web Service to establish an identifier for a patient.
Remarks: Text based result content, such as narratives, impressions, or addendums, will be represented as related Observations rather than in the text element inherited by DomainResource. If the results from a Search return medication orders, an error will be returned for those orders.

category.Name: category
category.Description:
The service category.

  • Starting in the November 2021 version of Epic (or the August 2021 version with special updates), this can be either an Epic order type or a value from the US Core valueset for DiagnosticReport.
  • In earlier versions, this must be a value from the US Core valueset for DiagnosticReport.

code.Name: code
code.Description:
The code for the report as a whole, as opposed to codes for the atomic results, which are the names on the observation resource referred to from the result.
  • Starting in the November 2021 version of Epic, or the August 2021 version with special updates, this can be any code type associated with the procedures, including LOINC, CPT, SNOMED, or other code types mapped to a procedure in Epic.
  • In earlier versions, this can only be a LOINC code.

date.Name: date
date.Description: The date or date range the order was resulted.

identifier.Name: identifier
identifier.Description: An identifier for the report. This can be the Epic order ID or the accession number.

patient.Name: patient
patient.Description: The reference to a patient resource.
patient.Optional: Either patient or subject must be provided. If both are provided, they must reference the same patient.

subject.Name: subject
subject.Description: The reference to a patient resource.
subject.Optional: Either patient or subject must be provided. If both are provided, they must reference the same patient.

Bundle.Name: Bundle
Bundle.Description: Resource bundle. For more information, refer to the FHIR specification.

DiagnosticReport.Name: DiagnosticReport
DiagnosticReport.Description: An instance of the R4 DiagnosticReport resource.

category.Name: category
category.Description:
The service category. This can be an Epic order type or part of the US Core valueset for DiagnosticReport.

Starting in Epic version November 2021 (August 2021 by special update), also includes the LOINC codes or DiagnosticServiceSectionId when available.

code.Name: code
code.Description: The Name/Code for this diagnostic report.

effectiveDateTime.Name: effectiveDateTime
effectiveDateTime.Description: Clinically relevant time/time period for report.

encounter.Name: encounter
encounter.Description:
Encounter when the test was ordered.

This will be either a FHIR Encounter reference in the encounter.reference element, or an encounter CSN identifier in the encounter.identifier element.

identifier.Name: identifier
identifier.Description: The business identifier for the report.

issued.Name: issued
issued.Description:
DateTime this version was released.

Available starting in the February 2022 version of Epic and in the November 2021 version with special updates.

performer.Name: performer
performer.Description: Participants in producing the report. This always includes one or more references to the Practitioner resource. Starting in the May 2022 version of Epic or the February 2022 version by special update, this element can also include a reference to an Organization resource.

presentedForm.Name: presentedForm
presentedForm.Description:
Shows links to the entire Binary textual results of the report.

Available starting in the November 2021 version of Epic and in the August 2021 version with special updates.

title.Name: title
title.Description: Label to display in place of the data.

url.Name: url
url.Description: Binary link for the textual content.

result.Name: result
result.Description: Observations, simple or complex nested groups.

SmartData.Name: extension
SmartData.Description: A data entity that captures a value. This element is available starting in the February 2022 version of Epic.

status.Name: status
status.Description: The status of the report. You can find the list of values here: http://hl7.org/fhir/diagnostic-report-status.
